The paper deals with data replication technologies and their consistency, which are topics related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and databases (cs.DB). The algorithms presented in the paper involve constructing operation graphs and analyzing read/write traces, which are typical tasks in data structures (cs.DS) and logic in computer science (cs.LO). Finally, the paper also discusses the complexity of the problem, which is a common theme in software engineering (cs.SE).
